{"title_page": "Daneil Cyrus", "text_new": "{{Cleanup bare URLs |bot=wp:tagbot |requester=User:Mdaniels5757 |date=April 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name                = Daneil Cyrus\n| image               = USMNT vs. Trinidad and Tobago (48125021277) (cropped).jpg\n| caption             = Cyrus with [[Trinidad and Tobago national football team|Trinidad and Tobago]] at the [[2019 CONCACAF Gold Cup]]\n| fullname            = Daneil Cyrus\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1990|12|15|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Plymouth, Trinidad and Tobago|Plymouth]], [[Trinidad and Tobago]]\n| height              = {{height|m=1.92}} \n| position            = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| currentclub         = [[Mohun Bagan]]\n| clubnumber          = 45\n| youthyears1         = 2008\u20132009\n| youthclubs1         = Stokely Vale fc\n| years1              = 2010\u20132012\n| clubs1              = 1. FC Santa Rosa\n| caps1               = 3\n| goals1              = 0\n| years2              = 2011\n| clubs2              = \u2192 [[Caledonia AIA]] (loan) \n| caps2               = 5\n| goals2              = 1\n| years3              = 2011\n| clubs3              = \u2192 [[Sporting Kansas City]] (loan) \n| caps3               = 2\n| goals3              = 0\n| years4              = 2012\u20132017\n| clubs4              = [[W Connection F.C.|W Connection]] \n| caps4               = 21\n| goals4              = 0\n| years5              = 2014\n| clubs5              = \u2192 [[Hanoi T&T F.C.|H\u00e0 N\u1ed9i T&T]] (loan) \n| caps5               = 26\n| goals5              = 1\n| years6              = 2015\n| clubs6              = \u2192 [[Chicago Fire Soccer Club|Chicago Fire]] (loan) \n| caps6               = 4\n| goals6              = 0\n| years7              = 2017\u20132018\n| clubs7              = [[Juticalpa F.C.|Juticalpa]]\n| caps7               = 29\n| goals7              = 0\n|years8               = 2018\u20132019\n|clubs8               = [[Al-Orobah F.C.|Al-Orobah]]\n|caps8                = 31\n|goals8               = 2\n|clubs9               = [[Mohun Bagan]]\n|years9               = 2019\u2013\n|caps9                = 8\n|goals9               = 1\n| nationalyears1     = 2007\n| nationalyears2     = 2009\n| nationalyears3     = 2010-2011\n| nationalyears4     = 2010\u2013\n| nationalteam1      = [[Trinidad and Tobago national under-17 football team|Trinidad and Tobago U-17]]\n| nationalteam2      = [[Trinidad and Tobago national under-20 football team|Trinidad and Tobago U-20]]\n| nationalteam3      = [[Trinidad and Tobago national under-23 football team |Trinidad and Tobago U-23]]\n| nationalteam4      = [[Trinidad and Tobago national football team|Trinidad and Tobago]]\n| nationalcaps1       = 3\n| nationalcaps2       = 3\n| nationalcaps3       = 2\n| nationalcaps4       = 90\n| nationalgoals1      = 0\n| nationalgoals2      = 0\n| nationalgoals3      = 0\n| nationalgoals4      = 0\n| club-update         = 5 December 2019\n| nationalteam-update = 5 December 2019\n}}\n\n'''Daneil Cyrus''' (born 15 December 1990), is a Trinidadian professional [[association football|football]] player<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.socawarriors.net/mens-senior-team/fixtures-results.html?view=playerprofile&id=563|title=Soca Warriors|accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref> who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for [[Mohun Bagan AC]] in [[I-League|I-league]] and [[Trinidad and Tobago national football team]].\n\n== Professional ==\nCyrus was born in [[Plymouth, Trinidad and Tobago|Plymouth]], [[Trinidad and Tobago]]. He was waived by [[Sporting Kansas City]] in February 2012 after spending part of the 2011 season with the [[Major League Soccer]] club.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportingkc.com/news/2012/02/weekly-update-february-22-2012|title=Weekly Update: February 22, 2012|work=Sporting Kansas City}}</ref> In July 2012 he signed for [[W Connection F.C.|W Connection]] in the [[TT Pro League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ttproleague.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1271:connection-hits-the-plus-sign-with-cyrus&catid=1:domestic-news&Itemid=2|title=Trinidad and Tobago Professional Football League - ttproleague -|work=ttproleague.com}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2014, Cyrus went on loan to [[V.League 1]] side [[Hanoi T&T F.C.|H\u00e0 N\u1ed9i T&T]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://thethao.thanhnien.vn/pages/20140519/Tuyen-thu-Trinidad-Tobago-dau-quan-cho-Ha-Noi-T-T.aspx|title=Tuy\u1ec3n th\u1ee7 Trinidad & Tobago \u0111\u1ea7u qu\u00e2n cho H\u00e0 N\u1ed9i T&T|date=19 May 2014|website=B\u00e1o Thanh Ni\u00ean|accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 August 2015, [[Chicago Fire Soccer Club|Chicago Fire]] acquired Cyrus on loan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chicago-fire.com/news/2015/08/chicago-fire-acquire-defender-daneil-cyrus|title=Chicago Fire Acquire Defender Daneil Cyrus|work=Chicago Fire}}</ref>. On August 2019, he was signed by\u00a0[[Mohun Bagan]]\u00a0to play in the\u00a0[[I-League]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.sportskeeda.com/football/indian-football-transfers-mohun-bagan-sign-former-chicago-fire-defender-daniel-cyrus-as-their-fifth-foreigner |title=Indian Football Transfers: Mohun Bagan sign former Chicago Fire defender Daniel Cyrus as their fifth foreigner |access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{MLS|daneil-cyrus}}\n{{Mohun Bagan A.C. squad}}\n{{Navboxes colour\n| title       = Trinidad and Tobago squads\n| bg          = #ce1126\n| fg          = white\n| bordercolor = black\n| list1       =\n{{Trinidad and Tobago squad 2013 CONCACAF Gold Cup}}\n{{Trinidad and Tobago squad 2015 CONCACAF Gold Cup}}\n{{Trinidad and Tobago squad 2019 CONCACAF Gold Cup}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cyrus, Daneil}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Trinidad and Tobago footballers]]\n[[Category:Trinidad and Tobago international footballers]]\n[[Category:TT Pro League players]]\n[[Category:Morvant Caledonia United players]]\n[[Category:Sporting Kansas City players]]\n[[Category:W Connection F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Chicago Fire FC players]]\n[[Category:H\u00e0 N\u1ed9i F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Juticalpa F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Al-Orobah FC players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate soccer players in the United States]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Vietnam]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Saudi Arabia]]\n[[Category:Major League Soccer players]]\n[[Category:Prince Mohammad bin Salman League players]]\n[[Category:2013 CONCACAF Gold Cup players]]\n[[Category:2014 Caribbean Cup players]]\n[[Category:2015 CONCACAF Gold Cup players]]\n[[Category:Trinidad and Tobago expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Trinidad and Tobago expatriate sportspeople in the United States]]\n[[Category:Trinidad and Tobago expatriate sportspeople in Vietnam]]\n[[Category:2009 CONCACAF U-20 Championship players]]\n[[Category:2019 CONCACAF Gold Cup players]]\n\n\n{{Trinidad-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Cleanup bare URLs |bot=wp:tagbot |requester=User:Mdaniels5757 |date=April 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name                = Daneil Cyrus\n| image               = USMNT vs. Trinidad and Tobago (48125021277) (cropped).jpg\n| caption             = Cyrus with [[Trinidad and Tobago national football team|Trinidad and Tobago]] at the [[2019 CONCACAF Gold Cup]]\n| fullname            = Daneil Cyrus\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1990|12|15|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Plymouth, Trinidad and Tobago|Plymouth]], [[Trinidad and Tobago]]\n| height              = {{height|m=1.92}} \n| position            = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| currentclub         = [[Mohun Bagan]]\n| clubnumber          = 45\n| youthyears1         = 2008\u20132009\n| youthclubs1         = Stokely Vale fc\n| years1              = 2010\u20132012\n| clubs1 