lgoals3      = 0\n| nationalgoals4      = 0\n| club-update         = 5 December 2019\n| nationalteam-update = 5 December 2019\n}}\n\n'''Daneil Cyrus''' (born 15 December 1990), is a Trinidadian professional [[association football|football]] player<ref>[http://www.socawarriors.net/mens-senior-team/fixtures-results.html?view=playerprofile&id=563 Soca Warriors]</ref> who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for [[Mohun Bagan AC]] in [[I-League|I-league]] and [[Trinidad and Tobago national football team]].\n\n== Professional ==\nCyrus was born in [[Plymouth, Trinidad and Tobago|Plymouth]], [[Trinidad and Tobago]]. He was waived by [[Sporting Kansas City]] in February 2012 after spending part of the 2011 season with the [[Major League Soccer]] club.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportingkc.com/news/2012/02/weekly-update-february-22-2012|title=Weekly Update: February 22, 2012|work=Sporting Kansas City}}</ref> In July 2012 he signed for [[W Connection F.C.|W Connection]] in the [[TT Pro League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ttproleague.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1271:connection-hits-the-plus-sign-with-cyrus&catid=1:domestic-news&Itemid=2|title=Trinidad and Tobago Professional Football League - ttproleague -|work=ttproleague.com}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2014, Cyrus went on loan to [[V.League 1]] side [[Hanoi T&T F.C.|H\u00e0 N\u1ed9i T&T]].<ref>[http://thethao.thanhnien.com.vn/pages/20140519/tuyen-thu-trinidad-tobago-dau-quan-cho-ha-noi-t-t.aspx Tuy\u1ec3n th\u1ee7 Trinidad & Tobago \u0111\u1ea7u qu\u00e2n cho H\u00e0 N\u1ed9i T&T] {{in lang|vi}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 August 2015, [[Chicago Fire Soccer Club|Chicago Fire]] acquired Cyrus on loan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chicago-fire.com/news/2015/08/chicago-fire-acquire-defender-daneil-cyrus|title=Chicago Fire Acquire Defender Daneil Cyrus|work=Chicago Fire}}</ref>. On August 2019, he was signed by\u00a0[[Mohun Bagan]]\u00a0to play in the\u00a0[[I-League]].<ref>https://www.sportskeeda.com/football/indian-football-transfers-mohun-bagan-sign-former-chicago-fire-defender-daniel-cyrus-as-their-fifth-foreigner</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{MLS|daneil-cyrus}}\n{{Mohun Bagan A.C. squad}}\n{{Navboxes colour\n| title       = Trinidad and Tobago squads\n| bg          = #ce1126\n| fg          = white\n| bordercolor = black\n| list1       =\n{{Trinidad and Tobago squad 2013 CONCACAF Gold Cup}}\n{{Trinidad and Tobago squad 2015 CONCACAF Gold Cup}}\n{{Trinidad and Tobago squad 2019 CONCACAF Gold Cup}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cyrus, Daneil}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Trinidad and Tobago footballers]]\n[[Category:Trinidad and Tobago international footballers]]\n[[Category:TT Pro League players]]\n[[Category:Morvant Caledonia United players]]\n[[Category:Sporting Kansas City players]]\n[[Category:W Connection F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Chicago Fire FC players]]\n[[Category:H\u00e0 N\u1ed9i F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Juticalpa F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Al-Orobah FC players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate soccer players in the United States]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Vietnam]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Saudi Arabia]]\n[[Category:Major League Soccer players]]\n[[Category:Prince Mohammad bin Salman League players]]\n[[Category:2013 CONCACAF Gold Cup players]]\n[[Category:2014 Caribbean Cup players]]\n[[Category:2015 CONCACAF Gold Cup players]]\n[[Category:Trinidad and Tobago expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Trinidad and Tobago expatriate sportspeople in the United States]]\n[[Category:Trinidad and Tobago expatriate sportspeople in Vietnam]]\n[[Category:2009 CONCACAF U-20 Championship players]]\n[[Category:2019 CONCACAF Gold Cup players]]\n\n\n{{Trinidad-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Mdaniels5757", "label": "safe", "comment": "Filled in 3 bare reference(s) with reFill 2- Reference edited withProveIt", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daneil_Cyrus"}
{"title_page": "Johnatan Bakalchuk", "text_new": "{{dead end|date=April 2020}}\n\n'''Johnatan Bakalchuk''' (born 1998) is an Israeli chess International Master since 2018 and a FIDE Master since 2014. He is ranked 39th best Israeli player.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ratings.fide.com/card.phtml?event=2810301|title=Bakalchuk, Johnatan FIDE Chess Profile - Players Arbiters Trainers|website=ratings.fide.com|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> His highest rating was 2471 (in March 2019).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://chess-db.com/public/pinfo.jsp?id=2810301|title=Johnatan Bakalchuk chess games and profile|last=|first=|date=|website=Chess DB|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nHe won the Israeli Junior Championships in 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chess.org.il/Tournaments/PlayerInTournament.aspx?Id=308731|title=\u05d4\u05d0\u05d9\u05d2\u05d5\u05d3 \u05d4\u05d9\u05e9\u05e8\u05d0\u05dc\u05d9 \u05dc\u05e9\u05d7\u05de\u05d8|website=www.chess.org.il|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\nHe won 2nd place in the Israeli U16 championship in 2013 and in 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chess.org.il/Tournaments/PlayerInTournament.aspx?Id=109778|title=\u05d4\u05d0\u05d9\u05d2\u05d5\u05d3 \u05d4\u05d9\u05e9\u05e8\u05d0\u05dc\u05d9 \u05dc\u05e9\u05d7\u05de\u05d8|website=www.chess.org.il|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chess.org.il/Tournaments/PlayerInTournament.aspx?Id=117472|title=\u05d4\u05d0\u05d9\u05d2\u05d5\u05d3 \u05d4\u05d9\u05e9\u05e8\u05d0\u05dc\u05d9 \u05dc\u05e9\u05d7\u05de\u05d8|website=www.chess.org.il|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\nHe won 1st place in the Israeli U11 championship in 2009.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chess.org.il/Tournaments/PlayerInTournament.aspx?Id=83253|title=\u05d4\u05d0\u05d9\u05d2\u05d5\u05d3 \u05d4\u05d9\u05e9\u05e8\u05d0\u05dc\u05d9 \u05dc\u05e9\u05d7\u05de\u05d8|website=www.chess.org.il|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\nHe beat GM [[Mikhail Antipov]] in the fifth round of the European championship in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.europechess.org/major-upsets-in-jerusalem-after-5-rounds/|title=MAJOR UPSETS IN JERUSALEM AFTER 5 ROUNDS|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n\n{{stub}}{{cat improve|date=April 2020}}\n", "text_old": "{{dead end|date=April 2020}}\n\n'''Johnatan Bakalchuk''' (born 1998) is an Israeli chess International Master since 2018 and a FIDE Master since 2014. He is ranked 39th best Israeli player.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ratings.fide.com/card.phtml?event=2810301|title=Bakalchuk, Johnatan FIDE Chess Profile - Players Arbiters Trainers|website=ratings.fide.com|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> His highest rating was 2471 (in March 2019).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://chess-db.com/public/pinfo.jsp?id=2810301|title=Johnatan Bakalchuk chess games and profile|last=|first=|date=|website=Chess DB|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nHe won the Israeli Junior Championships in 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chess.org.il/Tournaments/PlayerInTournament.aspx?Id=308731|title=\u05d4\u05d0\u05d9\u05d2\u05d5\u05d3 \u05d4\u05d9\u05e9\u05e8\u05d0\u05dc\u05d9 \u05dc\u05e9\u05d7\u05de\u05d8|website=www.chess.org.il|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\nHe won 2nd place in the Israeli U16 championship in 2013 and in 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chess.org.il/Tournaments/PlayerInTournament.aspx?Id=109778|title=\u05d4\u05d0\u05d9\u05d2\u05d5\u05d3 \u05d4\u05d9\u05e9\u05e8\u05d0\u05dc\u05d9 \u05dc\u05e9\u05d7\u05de\u05d8|website=www.chess.org.il|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chess.org.il/Tournaments/PlayerInTournament.aspx?Id=117472|title=\u05d4\u05d0\u05d9\u05d2\u05d5\u05d3 \u05d4\u05d9\u05e9\u05e8\u05d0\u05dc\u05d9 \u05dc\u05e9\u05d7\u05de\u05d8|website=www.chess.org.il|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\nHe won 1st place in the Israeli U11 championship in 2009.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chess.org.il/Tournaments/PlayerInTournament.aspx?Id=83253|title=\u05d4\u05d0\u05d9\u05d2\u05d5\u05d3 \u05d4\u05d9\u05e9\u05e8\u05d0\u05dc\u05d9 \u05dc\u05e9\u05d7\u05de\u05d8|website=www.chess.org.il|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\nHe beat GM [[Mikhail Antipov]] in the fifth round of the European championship in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.europechess.org/major-upsets-in-jerusalem-after-5-rounds/|title=MAJOR UPSETS IN JERUSALEM AFTER 5 ROUNDS|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n\n{{stub}}{{cat improve|date=April 2020}}\n", "name_user": "Bensci54", "label": "safe", "comment": "add references heading", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Johnatan_Bakalchuk"}
{"title_page": "Evaristo de Miranda", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Orphan|date=July 2015}}\n{{autobiography|date=April 2014}}\n{{external links|date=July 2015}}\n}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2014}}\n\n{{Infobox writer\n|name          =Evaristo Eduardo de Miranda \n|image         =Evaristo Eduardo de Miranda.jpg\n|alt           =Evaristo Eduardo de Miranda.\n|birth_date    ={{birth date and age|1952|07|17}} \n|birth_place   =S\u00e3o Paulo, SP\n|nationality   =Brazilian\n|occupation    =Writer and researcher\n|partner       =[http://www.portaldosjornalistas.com.br/perfil.aspx?id=9038 Liana John]\n}}\n\n'''Evaristo Eduardo de Miranda''' is a Brazilian writer and researcher at [[Embrapa]]. He is an expert in agriculture, ecology, environment and [[land management]].\n\n== Career ==\n\nEvaristo E. de Miranda graduated in Agronomy in France (1976) and did his MS and PhD in ecology at the [[Montpellier University]]. His master and doctoral thesis were performed in the region of Maradi, [[Niger]] (Africa). In 1980, he joined [http://www.cpatsa.embrapa.br Embrapa Semiarid], in Petrolina, Pernambuco state, as a researcher. He established and directed three National Research Centres at Embrapa, as Embrapa Monitoring Satellite; and actually he is the coordinator of the Strategic Territorial Intelligence Group (GITE/Embrapa) and General Head of [https://www.embrapa.br/en/web/portal/team/-/empregado/185062/evaristo-eduardo-de-miranda Embrapa Territorial Intelligence].\n\nHe was a professor at the Pernambuco Federal Rural University Botany Institute (UFRPE/IB) and at the S\u00e3o Paulo University Biosciences Institute (IB/USP). He is member of several scientific societies. He also served as a consultant on the UN World Conference on the Environment, Rio 92. With hundreds of scientific and disclosure articles, published either in Brazil or abroad, Evaristo de Miranda is author and co-authot of more than 40 books in Portuguese, English, Italian, French, Spanish and Mandarin.\n \nHe began his career<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvcultura.cmais.com.br/reportereco/o-perfil-do-cientista-evaristo-de-miranda-1 |title=Entrevista: O perfil do cientista Evaristo de Miranda. TV Cultura, maio de 2010}}</ref> as a writer on humanity issues with the books \"Water, Breath and Light\" (1995), \"Now and at the Hour\" (1996), \"Body, Territory of the Sacred\" (2000) and \"Wise Pharisees\" (2001), also translated in Italy and France. Recently he published \"The Intimate and the Infinite\",\"300 reasons to baptize\",\"Will understand these Catholics\",\"Bible - history, curiosities and contradictions\" and \"The Lord Bom Jesus of Monte Alegre do Sul\". Among his books of Ecology and Agriculture stand out \n\"Shades of Green: the sustainability of agriculture in Brazil (2018)\", \"Agriculture in Brazil in the XXI Century \" (2013), \"Jaguar\" (2010 ) and \"Botanical Gardens in Brazil\" (2009).\n\nHis scientific and literary production is multipurpose, it addresses topics such as wildlife<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aelrj.org.br/website2010/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=25:rio-de-livros-por-hermano-vianna&catid=9:publicacoes&Itemid=17 |title=Mat\u00e9ria: Rio de Livros (Jaguar). O Globo, maio de 2011}}</ref> and domestic animals;<ref>{{cite web |url=http://viajeaqui.abril.com.br/materias/cachorro-vira-lata/ |title=Mat\u00e9ria: Um velho companheiro. National Geographic, mar\u00e7o de 2010 |access-date=9 April 2014 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20140402141448/http://viajeaqui.abril.com.br/materias/cachorro-vira-lata/ |archive-date=2 April 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.icnews.com.br/2011.04.07/colunistas/aroldo-mura/o-cavalo-anfibio-do-pantanal-e-revelado-por-evaristo-cientista-e-crente/ |title=Mat\u00e9ria: O cavalo anf\u00edbio do Pantanal \u00e9 revelado por Evaristo, cientista e crente. IC News, abril de 2011 |access-date=9 April 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407094650/http://www.icnews.com.br/2011.04.07/colunistas/aroldo-mura/o-cavalo-anfibio-do-pantanal-e-revelado-por-evaristo-cientista-e-crente/ |archive-date=7 April 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Brazilian ecosystems<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cienciaefe.org.br/jornal/ed88/livro.html |title=Mat\u00e9ria: Lan\u00e7amento do Livro Quando o Amazonas corria para o Pac\u00edfico. Jornal Universidade, fevereiro de 2007 |access-date=9 April 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303175306/http://www.cienciaefe.org.br/jornal/ed88/livro.html |archive-date=3 March 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://viajeaqui.abril.com.br/materias/fotografo-fabio-colombini-lanca-livro-sobre-mata-atlantica-em-sao-paulo-noticias |title=Mat\u00e9ria: A Arte do Olhar \u2013 Mata Atl\u00e2ntica ser\u00e1 lan\u00e7ado nesta quinta-feira, em S\u00e3o Paulo. National Geographic, outubro de 2012 |access-date=9 April 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407120144/http://viajeaqui.abril.com.br/materias/fotografo-fabio-colombini-lanca-livro-sobre-mata-atlantica-em-sao-paulo-noticias |archive-date=7 April 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and their History;<ref>{{cite web |url=http://vejario.abril.com.br/especial/reportagens/quando-plantas-valiam-ouro-630637.shtml |title=Mat\u00e9ria: Quando plantas valiam ouro. Veja Rio, junho de 2011 |access-date=9 April 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407115551/http://vejario.abril.com.br/especial/reportagens/quando-plantas-valiam-ouro-630637.shtml |archive-date=7 April 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://planetasustentavel.abril.com.br/noticia/atitude/conteudo_232862.shtml |title=Mat\u00e9ria: A inven\u00e7\u00e3o do Brasil. Planeta Sustent\u00e1vel, maio de 2007 |access-date=9 April 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407115502/http://planetasustentavel.abril.com.br/noticia/atitude/conteudo_232862.shtml |archive-date=7 April 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Cartography<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cdbrasil.cnpm.embrapa.br |title=Projeto: Brasil Visto do Espa\u00e7o. Embrapa, junho de 2004}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.relevobr.cnpm.embrapa.br/ |title=Projeto: Brasil em Relevo. Embrapa, junho de 2006}}</ref> and satellite monitoring of the vegetation and the environment.<ref>Miranda, E. E. et al. Vegetation Map of South America. Luxemburgo: European Commission, 2002. 48p.</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.queimadas.cnpm.embrapa.br/ |title=Projeto: Monitoramento Orbital de Queimadas. Embrapa, maio de 2010}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvuol.uol.com.br/video/canal-livre-sobre-gestao-territorial-sera-reapresentado-pelo-04024C9B3460DC993326// |title=Entrevista: Gest\u00e3o Territorial. Canal LIvre, setembro de 2012}}</ref> He also deals with spirituality<ref name=\"animais_interiores\">{{cite web |url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/folha/ilustrada/ult90u33783.shtml |title=Mat\u00e9ria: Livro ensina a reconhecer os animais que habitam cada pessoa. Folha de S.Paulo, junho de 2003}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ihuonline.unisinos.br/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=2459&secao=288 |title=Mat\u00e9ria: As \u00e1guas e a sede do humano pela sua humanidade e divindade. Revista do Instituto Humanitas Unisinos, abril de 2009}}</ref>\nand philosophical issues.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.estadao.com.br/arquivo/arteelazer/2000/not20000809p2530.htm |title=Mat\u00e9ria: O corpo na vis\u00e3o judaico-crist\u00e3.O Estad\u00e3o, agosto de 2000}}</ref>\n\nFor 8 years, Evaristo de Miranda had a participation in the weekly program [https://web.archive.org/web/20160625055027/http://www.caminhosdaroca.tv.br/ Caminhos da Ro\u00e7a] (Rural Paths) at EPTV \u2013 Globo Network and is an agroculture commentator at Rede Bandeirantes de R\u00e1dio e Televis\u00e3o. He regularly publishes in newspapers and magazines such as [https://web.archive.org/web/20140407115502/http://planetasustentavel.abril.com.br/noticia/atitude/conteudo_232862.shtml National Geographic], [http://www.eco21.com.br/textos/textos.asp?ID=3187 ECO 21],[http://issuu.com/eriklm/docs/agro_ed_49_04271e7c70d850?e=5757079/5190975 AgroDBO], [http://www.cienciaefe.org.br/jornal-universidade/ Jornal da Universidade], [https://www.atribuna.com.br/variedades/atrevista A Tribuna], [http://www.agroanalysis.com.br/ Agroanalysis] and [http://www.estadao.com.br/noticias/impresso,agricultura-e-aquecimento-verbal,1144394,0.htm O Estado de S. Paulo].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://acervo.estadao.com.br/pagina/#!/20060611-41144-nac-208-ali-j4-not |title=Mat\u00e9ria: Preservar \u00e9 derrubar os mitos. Ali\u00e1s, O Estado de S. Paulo, junho de 2006}}</ref>\n\n== Bibliography in Brazil ==\n*''Tons de verde: a sustentabilidade da agricultura no Brasil (2018)''\n*Shades of Green - Sustainable Agriculture in Brazil (2018)\n*''Agropecu\u00e1ria no Brasil: uma s\u00edntese (2017)''\n*''O Senhor Bom Jesus de Monte Alegre do Sul (2016)''\n*''Rios do Brasil (2016)''\n*''A geografia da pele - um brasileiro imerso na \u00c1frica profunda (2015)''\n*''B\u00edblia \u2013 hist\u00f3ria, curiosidades e contradi\u00e7\u00f5es (2015)''\n*''Vai entender esses cat\u00f3licos..''. (2014)\n*''Eu vim para servir - comunidade, Igreja e sociedade'' (2014).\n* ''Agricultura no Brasil no S\u00e9culo XXI'' (2013).\n* ''Caub\u00f3is do Pantanal'' (2013).\n* ''Quando os jovens n\u00e3o tinham voz, nem vez: Jesus no conflito de gera\u00e7\u00f5es'' (2013).\n* ''A Arte do Olhar \u2013 Mata Atl\u00e2ntica'' (2012).\n* ''300 Raz\u00f5es para Batizar'' (2011).\n* ''Jaguar. O rei das Am\u00e9ricas'' (2010).\n* ''O \u00cdntimo e o Infinito \u2013 O Universo das Ci\u00eancias e o Cosmos das Religi\u00f5es'' (2010).\n* ''Embrapa Monitoramento por Sat\u00e9lite \u2013 20 anos'' (2009).\n* ''Jardins Bot\u00e2nicos do Brasil''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvcultura.cmais.com.br/reportereco/videos/livro-relata-historias-e-curiosidades-dos-jardins-botanicos-do-brasil |title=Mat\u00e9ria: Livro relata hist\u00f3rias e curiosidades dos Jardins Bot\u00e2nicos do Brasil. Rep\u00f3rter Eco, TV Cultura, maio de 2010}}</ref>{{Dead link|date=April 2020}}(2009).\n* ''Quando o Amazonas corria para o Pac\u00edfico, uma hist\u00f3ria desconhecida da Amaz\u00f4nia'' (2007).\n* ''Guia de Curiosidades Cat\u00f3licas''<ref>Entrevista: Pesquisador fala sobre o lan\u00e7amento do livro \"Guia de Curiosidades Cat\u00f3licas\". Rede Globo \u2013 Programa do J\u00f4, dezembro de 2007.</ref>(2007).\n* ''Natureza Brasileira em Detalhe''<ref>Entrevista: Pesquisador fala sobre o lan\u00e7amento do livro \"Natureza, Conserva\u00e7\u00e3o e Cultura\". Rede Globo \u2013 Programa do J\u00f4, agosto de 2003.</ref>(2006).\n* ''Maravilhas a Caminho \u2013 Acolher um deficiente, viver nossas defici\u00eancias'' (2005).\n* ''A \u00e1gua na natureza e na vida dos homens'' (2004).\n* ''O Descobrimento da Biodiversidade \u2013 A Ecologia de \u00cdndios, Jesu\u00edtas e Leigos no S\u00e9culo XVI'' (2004).\n* ''A Sacralidade das \u00c1guas Corporais'' (2004).\n* ''Animais Interiores \u2013 nadadores e rastejantes'' (2004).\n* ''Animais Interiores \u2013 Os voadores'' (2003).\n* ''Natureza, conserva\u00e7\u00e3o e cultura; ensaio sobre a rela\u00e7\u00e3o do homem com a natureza no Brasil'' (2003).\n* ''S\u00e1bios Fariseus \u2013 Reparar uma Injusti\u00e7a'' (2001).\n* ''Corpo Territ\u00f3rio do Sagrado'' (2000).\n* ''A Foice da Lua no Campo das Estrelas \u2013 Ministrar Ex\u00e9quias'' (1998).\n* ''Agora e na Hora \u2013 Ritos de passagem \u00e0 eternidade'' (1996).\n* ''\u00c1gua, Sopro e Luz \u2013 Alquimia do Batismo'' (1995).\n* ''A Ecologia' (1995).''\n\n== Bibliography in other countries ==\n\n* ''La d\u00e9couverte de la biodiversit\u00e9'' (2008), French.\n* ''Il Corpo \u2013 Territorio del sacro'' (2002), Italian.\n* ''Farisei Nostri Maestri \u2013 Un pregiudizio da superare'' (2001), Italian.\n* ''Sages Pharisiens \u2013 R\u00e9parer une Injustice'' (2001), French.\n* ''Acqua, Soffio e Luce \u2013 Riflessioni sui Simboli del Battesimo'' (1999), Italian.\n* ''Essai sur les d\u00e9s\u00e9quilibres \u00e9cologiques et agricoles en zone tropicale semi-aride: le cas de la r\u00e9gion de Maradi au Niger'' (1980), French.\n\n== Awards and titles ==\n\n* ''Medalha Ex\u00e9rcito Brasileiro - Ex\u00e9rcito Brasileiro (2018)''\n* ''Ordem do M\u00e9rito Aeron\u00e1utico - For\u00e7a \u00c1rea Brasileira (FAB) \u2013 Minist\u00e9rio da Defesa (2018)''\n* ''Pr\u00eamio 100 Personalidades Mais Influentes do Agroneg\u00f3cio \u2013 Categoria \u201cUniversidade e Pesquisa\u201d- Revista Dinheiro Rural (2018)''\n* ''Pr\u00eamio CNA Agro Brasil Pesquisa (2018)''\n*Pr\u00eamio Canacampo e SIAMIG - Reconhecimento aos relevantes servi\u00e7os prestados ao agroneg\u00f3cio brasileiro - no 10\u00ba Megacana Tech Show (2018).\n*''Pr\u00eamio ABC - Personalidade do ano em Ensino e Pesquisa (2017)''\n*''As 100 personalidades mais influentes do agroneg\u00f3cio, Revista Dinheiro Rural (2017)''\n*''Construtor da internet.br, Rede Nacional de Ensino e Pesquisa - RNP (2017)''\n*''Cidad\u00e3o Campineiro, C\u00e2mara Municipal de Campinas (2017)''\n*''Pr\u00eamio M\u00e9rito ABCZ, Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Brasileira de Criadores de Zebu - ABCZ (2016)''\n*Placa comemorativa II Semin\u00e1rio Solo e \u00c1gua, Companhia de Desenvolvimento dos Vales do S\u00e3o Francisco e do Parna\u00edba - Codevasf (2016)\n*''Pr\u00eamio M\u00e9rito Agropecu\u00e1rio, C\u00e2mara dos Deputados - Congresso Nacional'' (2014)\n*''Pr\u00eamio Institucional, Empresa Brasileira de Pesquisa Agropecu\u00e1ria \u2013 Embrapa'' (2010).\n* ''Pr\u00eamio Nacional de Equipes, Empresa Brasileira de Pesquisa Agropecu\u00e1ria \u2013 Embrapa'' (2009).\n* ''Pr\u00eamio Abril de Jornalismo: Categoria Ci\u00eancia<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.comciencia.br/comciencia/handler.php?section=8&edicao=37&id=450 |title=Mat\u00e9ria: Divulga\u00e7\u00e3o feita por quem produz ci\u00eancia. Com Ci\u00eancia, julho de 2008}}</ref>'' (2008).\n* ''Pr\u00eamio de Chefia, Empresa Brasileira de Pesquisa Agropecu\u00e1ria \u2013 Embrapa.'' (2007)\n* ''Chevalier du Cep, Ordre Universelle des Chevalliers du Cep \u2013 Montpellier'' (2004).\n* ''Pr\u00eamio Prof. Dr. Newton Freire-Maia, Instituto Ci\u00eancia e F\u00e9 (2002).''\n* ''Ordem do M\u00e9rito Militar, Ex\u00e9rcito Brasileiro'' (1998).\n* ''Ordem de Rio Branco, Minist\u00e9rio das Rela\u00e7\u00f5es Exteriores \u2013 Itamaraty'' (1988).\n* ''Cidad\u00e3o Noronhense, Governo de Fernando de Noronha'' (1987).\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Brazilian male writers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Orphan|date=July 2015}}\n{{autobiography|date=April 2014}}\n{{external links|date=July 2015}}\n}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2014}}\n\n{{Infobox writer\n|name          =Evaristo Eduardo de Miranda \n|image         =Evaristo Eduardo de Miranda.jpg\n|alt           =Evaristo Eduardo de Miranda.\n|birth_date    ={{birth date and age|1952|07|17}} \n|birth_place   =S\u00e3o Paulo, SP\n|nationality   =Brazilian\n|occupation    =Writer and researcher\n|partner       =[http://www.portaldosjornalistas.com.br/perfil.aspx?id=9038 Liana John]\n}}\n\n'''Evaristo Eduardo de Miranda''' is a Brazilian writer and researcher at [[Embrapa]]. He is an expert in agriculture, ecology, environment and [[land management]].\n\n== Career ==\n\nEvaristo E. de Miranda graduated in Agronomy in France (1976) and did his MS and PhD in ecology at the [[Montpellier University]]. His master and doctoral thesis were performed in the region of Maradi, [[Niger]] (Africa). In 1980, he joined Embrapa Semiarid, in Petrolina, Pernambuco state, as a researcher. In 1986 he moved to S\u00e3o Paulo state, where he established and directed three National Research Centres at Embrapa, including the NMA. He is the coordinator of strategic territorial intelligence \u2013 GITE Embrapa and General Head of Embrapa Territorial Intelligence.\n\nHe was a professor at the Pernambuco Federal Rural University Botany Institute (UFRPE/IB) and at the S\u00e3o Paulo University Biosciences Institute (IB/USP). He is member of several scientific societies. He also served as a consultant on the UN World Conference on the Environment, Rio 92. Evaristo de Miranda wrote hundreds of scientific articles, published either in Brazil or abroad. He is the author of more than 30 books.\n \nHe began his career<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvcultura.cmais.com.br/reportereco/o-perfil-do-cientista-evaristo-de-miranda-1 |title=Entrevista: O perfil do cientista Evaristo de Miranda. TV Cultura, maio de 2010}}</ref>{{Dead link|date=April 2020}} as a writer on humanity issues with the books \"Water, Breath and Light\" (1995), \"Now and at the Hour\" (1996), \"Body, Territory of the Sacred\" (2000) and \"Wise Pharisees\" (2001), also translated and published in Italy and France. Among his books of Ecology and Agriculture stand out \"Agriculture in Brazil in the XXI Century \" (2013), \"Jaguar\" (2010 ) and \"Botanical Gardens in Brazil\" (2009).\n\nHis scientific and literary production is multipurpose. It addresses topics such as wildlife<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aelrj.org.br/website2010/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=25:rio-de-livros-por-hermano-vianna&catid=9:publicacoes&Itemid=17 |title=Mat\u00e9ria: Rio de Livros (Jaguar). O Globo, maio de 2011}}</ref> and domestic animals;<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.icnews.com.br/2011.04.07/colunistas/aroldo-mura/o-cavalo-anfibio-do-pantanal-e-revelado-por-evaristo-cientista-e-crente/ |title=Mat\u00e9ria: O cavalo anf\u00edbio do Pantanal \u00e9 revelado por Evaristo, cientista e crente. IC News, abril de 2011 |access-date=9 April 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407094650/http://www.icnews.com.br/2011.04.07/colunistas/aroldo-mura/o-cavalo-anfibio-do-pantanal-e-revelado-por-evaristo-cientista-e-crente/ |archive-date=7 April 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Brazilian ecosystems<ref>{{cite web |url=http://viajeaqui.abril.com.br/materias/fotografo-fabio-colombini-lanca-livro-sobre-mata-atlantica-em-sao-paulo-noticias |title=Mat\u00e9ria: A Arte do Olhar \u2013 Mata Atl\u00e2ntica ser\u00e1 lan\u00e7ado nesta quinta-feira, em S\u00e3o Paulo. National Geographic, outubro de 2012 |access-date=9 April 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407120144/http://viajeaqui.abril.com.br/materias/fotografo-fabio-colombini-lanca-livro-sobre-mata-atlantica-em-sao-paulo-noticias |archive-date=7 April 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and their History; Cartography and satellite monitoring of the vegetation and the environment. He also deals with spirituality<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ihuonline.unisinos.br/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=2459&secao=288 |title=Mat\u00e9ria: As \u00e1guas e a sede do humano pela sua humanidade e divindade. Revista do Instituto Humanitas Unisinos, abril de 2009}}</ref>{{Dead link|date=April 2020}} and philosophical issues.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.estadao.com.br/arquivo/arteelazer/2000/not20000809p2530.htm |title=Mat\u00e9ria: O corpo na vis\u00e3o judaico-crist\u00e3.O Estad\u00e3o, agosto de 2000}}</ref>\n\nFor 6 years, Evaristo de Miranda had a participation in the weekly program Caminhos da Ro\u00e7a (Rural Paths) at EPTV \u2013 Globo Network. He frequently publishes articles in newspapers and magazines such as National Geographic, ECO 21,AgroDBO Agroanalysis e O Estado de S. Paulo.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://acervo.estadao.com.br/pagina/#!/20060611-41144-nac-208-ali-j4-not |title=Mat\u00e9ria: Preservar \u00e9 derrubar os mitos. Ali\u00e1s, O Estado de S. Paulo, junho de 2006}}</ref>\n\n== Bibliography in Brazil ==\n*''Tons de verde: a sustentabilidade da agricultura no Brasil (2018)''\n*Shades of Green - Sustainable Agriculture in Brazil (2018)\n*''Agropecu\u00e1ria no Brasil: uma s\u00edntese (2017)''\n*''O Senhor Bom Jesus de Monte Alegre do Sul (2016)''\n*''Rios do Brasil (2016)''\n*''A geografia da pele - um brasileiro imerso na \u00c1frica profunda (2015)''\n*''B\u00edblia \u2013 hist\u00f3ria, curiosidades e contradi\u00e7\u00f5es (2015)''\n*''Vai entender esses cat\u00f3licos..''. (2014)\n*''Eu vim para servir - comunidade, Igreja e sociedade'' (2014).\n* ''Agricultura no Brasil no S\u00e9culo XXI'' (2013).\n* ''Caub\u00f3is do Pantanal'' (2013).\n* ''Quando os jovens n\u00e3o tinham voz, nem vez: Jesus no conflito de gera\u00e7\u00f5es'' (2013).\n* ''A Arte do Olhar \u2013 Mata Atl\u00e2ntica'' (2012).\n* ''300 Raz\u00f5es para Batizar'' (2011).\n* ''Jaguar. O rei das Am\u00e9ricas'' (2010).\n* ''O \u00cdntimo e o Infinito \u2013 O Universo das Ci\u00eancias e o Cosmos das Religi\u00f5es'' (2010).\n* ''Embrapa Monitoramento por Sat\u00e9lite \u2013 20 anos'' (2009).\n* ''Jardins Bot\u00e2nicos do Brasil''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvcultura.cmais.com.br/reportereco/videos/livro-relata-historias-e-curiosidades-dos-jardins-botanicos-do-brasil |title=Mat\u00e9ria: Livro relata hist\u00f3rias e curiosidades dos Jardins Bot\u00e2nicos do Brasil. Rep\u00f3rter Eco, TV Cultura, maio de 2010}}</ref>{{Dead link|date=April 2020}}(2009).\n* ''Quando o Amazonas corria para o Pac\u00edfico, uma hist\u00f3ria desconhecida da Amaz\u00f4nia'' (2007).\n* ''Guia de Curiosidades Cat\u00f3licas''<ref>Entrevista: Pesquisador fala sobre o lan\u00e7amento do livro \"Guia de Curiosidades Cat\u00f3licas\". Rede Globo \u2013 Programa do J\u00f4, dezembro de 2007.</ref>(2007).\n* ''Natureza Brasileira em Detalhe''<ref>Entrevista: Pesquisador fala sobre o lan\u00e7amento do livro \"Natureza, Conserva\u00e7\u00e3o e Cultura\". Rede Globo \u2013 Programa do J\u00f4, agosto de 2003.</ref>(2006).\n* ''Maravilhas a Caminho \u2013 Acolher um deficiente, viver nossas defici\u00eancias'' (2005).\n* ''A \u00e1gua na natureza e na vida dos homens'' (2004).\n* ''O Descobrimento da Biodiversidade \u2013 A Ecologia de \u00cdndios, Jesu\u00edtas e Leigos no S\u00e9culo XVI'' (2004).\n* ''A Sacralidade das \u00c1guas Corporais'' (2004).\n* ''Animais Interiores \u2013 nadadores e rastejantes'' (2004).\n* ''Animais Interiores \u2013 Os voadores'' (2003).\n* ''Natureza, conserva\u00e7\u00e3o e cultura; ensaio sobre a rela\u00e7\u00e3o do homem com a natureza no Brasil'' (2003).\n* ''S\u00e1bios Fariseus \u2013 Reparar uma Injusti\u00e7a'' (2001).\n* ''Corpo Territ\u00f3rio do Sagrado'' (2000).\n* ''A Foice da Lua no Campo das Estrelas \u2013 Ministrar Ex\u00e9quias'' (1998).\n* ''Agora e na Hora \u2013 Ritos de passagem \u00e0 eternidade'' (1996).\n* ''\u00c1gua, Sopro e Luz \u2013 Alquimia do Batismo'' (1995).\n* ''A Ecologia' (1995).''\n\n== Bibliography in other countries ==\n\n* ''La d\u00e9couverte de la biodiversit\u00e9'' (2008), French.\n* ''Il Corpo \u2013 Territorio del sacro'' (2002), Italian.\n* ''Farisei Nostri Maestri \u2013 Un pregiudizio da superare'' (2001), Italian.\n* ''Sages Pharisiens \u2013 R\u00e9parer une Injustice'' (2001), French.\n* ''Acqua, Soffio e Luce \u2013 Riflessioni sui Simboli del Battesimo'' (1999), Italian.\n* ''Essai sur les d\u00e9s\u00e9quilibres \u00e9cologiques et agricoles en zone tropicale semi-aride: le cas de la r\u00e9gion de Maradi au Niger'' (1980), French.\n\n== Awards and titles ==\n\n* ''Medalha Ex\u00e9rcito Brasileiro - Ex\u00e9rcito Brasileiro (2018)''\n* ''Ordem do M\u00e9rito Aeron\u00e1utico - For\u00e7a \u00c1rea Brasileira (FAB) \u2013 Minist\u00e9rio da Defesa (2018)''\n* ''Pr\u00eamio 100 Personalidades Mais Influentes do Agroneg\u00f3cio \u2013 Categoria \u201cUniversidade e Pesquisa\u201d- Revista Dinheiro Rural (2018)''\n* ''Pr\u00eamio CNA Agro Brasil Pesquisa (2018)''\n*Pr\u00eamio Canacampo e SIAMIG - Reconhecimento aos relevantes servi\u00e7os prestados ao agroneg\u00f3cio brasileiro - no 10\u00ba Megacana Tech Show (2018).\n*''Pr\u00eamio ABC - Personalidade do ano em Ensino e Pesquisa (2017)''\n*''As 100 personalidades mais influentes do agroneg\u00f3cio, Revista Dinheiro Rural (2017)''\n*''Construtor da internet.br, Rede Nacional de Ensino e Pesquisa - RNP (2017)''\n*''Cidad\u00e3o Campineiro, C\u00e2mara Municipal de Campinas (2017)''\n*''Pr\u00eamio M\u00e9rito ABCZ, Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Brasileira de Criadores de Zebu - ABCZ (2016)''\n*Placa comemorativa II Semin\u00e1rio Solo e \u00c1gua, Companhia de Desenvolvimento dos Vales do S\u00e3o Francisco e do Parna\u00edba - Codevasf (2016)\n*''Pr\u00eamio M\u00e9rito Agropecu\u00e1rio, C\u00e2mara dos Deputados - Congresso Nacional'' (2014)\n*''Pr\u00eamio Institucional, Empresa Brasileira de Pesquisa Agropecu\u00e1ria \u2013 Embrapa'' (2010).\n* ''Pr\u00eamio Nacional de Equipes, Empresa Brasileira de Pesquisa Agropecu\u00e1ria \u2013 Embrapa'' (2009).\n* ''Pr\u00eamio Abril de Jornalismo: Categoria Ci\u00eancia<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.comciencia.br/comciencia/handler.php?section=8&edicao=37&id=450 |title=Mat\u00e9ria: Divulga\u00e7\u00e3o feita por quem produz ci\u00eancia. Com Ci\u00eancia, julho de 2008}}</ref>'' (2008).\n* ''Pr\u00eamio de Chefia, Empresa Brasileira de Pesquisa Agropecu\u00e1ria \u2013 Embrapa.'' (2007)\n* ''Chevalier du Cep, Ordre Universelle des Chevalliers du Cep \u2013 Montpellier'' (2004).\n* ''Pr\u00eamio Prof. Dr. Newton Freire-Maia, Instituto Ci\u00eancia e F\u00e9 (2002).''\n* ''Ordem do M\u00e9rito Militar, Ex\u00e9rcito Brasileiro'' (1998).\n* ''Ordem de Rio Branco, Minist\u00e9rio das Rela\u00e7\u00f5es Exteriores \u2013 Itamaraty'' (1988).\n* ''Cidad\u00e3o Noronhense, Governo de Fernando de Noronha'' (1987).\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Brazilian male writers]]\n", "name_user": "Evaristomiranda", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eCareer)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evaristo_de_Miranda"}
{"title_page": "Anthracotheriidae", "text_new": "{{Automatic taxobox\n| fossil_range = {{Fossil range|Middle Eocene|Late Pliocene}}\n| image = Anthracotherium magnum.jpg\n| image_upright = 1.15\n| image_caption = ''[[Anthracotherium]]''\n| taxon = Anthracotheriidae\n| authority = [[Joseph Leidy|Leidy]], 1869\n| subdivision_ranks = Subfamilies and genera<ref name=KronMan>{{cite book |last=Kron, D.G. |first=B. |author2=Manning, E. |editor1=Janis, C.M. |editor2=Scott, K.M. |editor3=Jacobs, L.L. |title=Evolution of Tertiary mammals of North America |edition= |year=1998 |publisher=Cambridge University Press |location=Cambridge |isbn=978-0-521-35519-3 |pages=381\u2013388 |chapter=Anthracotheriidae }}</ref><ref name=\"PNAS on Anthracotheres\">{{Cite journal |author1=Lihoreau, Fabrice |author2=Jean-Renaud Boisserie |display-authors=etal | title = Anthracothere dental anatomy reveals a late Miocene Chado-Libyan bioprovince | journal = [[Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences]] | issue = originally published online May 24, 2006 | language = |url=http://www.pnas.org/cgi/reprint/103/23/8763.pdf |doi=10.1073/pnas.0603126103 | pmid=16723392 | year = 2006 | volume = 103 | pages = 8763\u20137 | pmc = 1482652|bibcode = 2006PNAS..103.8763L }}</ref>\n| subdivision = \n\u2020 Anthracotheriinae\n*\u2020''[[Anthracotherium]]'' <small>([[type genus]])</small>\n*\u2020''[[Heptacodon]]''\n*\u2020''[[Siamotherium]]''\n\u2020 Bothriodontinae\n*\u2020''[[Aepinacodon]]''\n*\u2020''[[Afromeryx]]''\n*\u2020''[[Arretotherium]]''\n*\u2020''[[Brachyodus]]''\n*\u2020''[[Bothriogenys]]''\n*\u2020''[[Elomeryx]]''\n*\u2020''[[Hemimeryx]]''\n*\u2020''[[Kukusepasutanka]]''\n*\u2020''[[Libycosaurus]]''\n*\u2020''[[Merycopotamus]]''\n*\u2020''[[Sivameryx]]''\n\u2020 Microbunodontinae\n*\u2020''[[Anthracokeryx]]''\n*\u2020''[[Microbunodon]]''\n}}\n\n'''Anthracotheriidae''' is a family of extinct, [[hippopotamus]]-like [[artiodactyl]] [[ungulate]]s related to [[hippopotamus]]es and [[Cetacea|whale]]s. The oldest genus, ''[[Elomeryx]]'', first appeared during the middle [[Eocene]] in Asia. They thrived in Africa and Eurasia, with a few species ultimately entering [[North America]] during the [[Oligocene]]. They died out in Europe and Africa during the [[Miocene]], possibly due to a combination of climatic changes and competition with other artiodactyls, including pigs and true hippopotamuses.<ref name=\"zipcodezoo.com\">{{cite web|url=http://zipcodezoo.com/Key/Animalia/Anthracotheriidae_Family.asp |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-04-30 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090319081544/http://zipcodezoo.com/Key/Animalia/Anthracotheriidae_Family.asp |archivedate=2009-03-19 }}</ref> The youngest genus, ''[[Merycopotamus]]'', died out in Asia during the late [[Pliocene]]. The family is named after the first [[genus]] discovered, ''[[Anthracotherium]]'', which means \"coal beast\", as the first fossils of it were found in [[Paleogene]]-aged coal beds in [[France]]. Fossil remains of the anthracothere genus were discovered by the Harvard University and Geological Survey of Pakistan joint research project (Y-GSP) in the well-dated middle and late Miocene deposits of the [[Pothohar Plateau]] in northern Pakistan.<ref>[], Chaire de Pal\u00e9oanthropologie et de Pr\u00e9histoire, Coll\u00e8ge de France, 11 place Marcelin Berthelot, 75005 Paris, France \nCopyright 2007 The Palaeontological Association\n</ref>\n\nIn life, the average anthracothere would have resembled a skinny hippopotamus with a comparatively small, narrow head and most likely pig-like in general appearance.<ref>{{cite web\n  | last = Allaby\n  | first = Michael \n  | title = Anthracotheriidae\n  | work = A Dictionary of Zoology\n  | publisher =  Encyclopedia.com\n  | year = 1999\n  | url = http://www.encyclopedia.com/doc/1O8-Anthracotheriidae.html\n  | doi =\n  | accessdate = 15 Apr 2009}}</ref> They had four or five toes on each foot, and broad feet suited to walking on soft mud. They had full sets of about 44 teeth with five semicrescentric cusps on the upper molars,<ref name=\"zipcodezoo.com\" /> which, in some species, were adapted for digging up the roots of aquatic plants.<ref>{{cite book |editor=Palmer, D.|year=1999 |title= The Marshall Illustrated Encyclopedia of Dinosaurs and Prehistoric Animals|publisher= Marshall Editions| location=London|isbn= 978-1-84028-152-1 |author1=Douglas Palmer |author2=consultant editor Barry Cox |page= 268}}</ref>\n\n==Evolutionary relationships==\n[[File:Microbunodon.JPG|thumb|left|''Microbunodon'' skull]]\nSome skeletal characters of anthracotheres suggest they are related to hippos.<ref name=\"Cetartiodactyla\">{{cite journal |last=Boisserie |first=Jean-Renaud |author2= Fabrice Lihoreau |author3=Michel Brunet |date=February 2005|title= The position of Hippopotamidae within Cetartiodactyla|journal= [[Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences]] |volume= 102 |issue= 5|pages= 1537\u20131541|doi= 10.1073/pnas.0409518102 |pmid=15677331 |pmc=547867|bibcode = 2005PNAS..102.1537B }}</ref>\nThe nature of the sediments in which they are fossilized implies they were amphibious, which supports the view, based on anatomical evidence, that they were ancestors of the hippopotamuses.<ref>Michael Allaby. \"Anthracotheriidae.\" ''A Dictionary of Zoology''. 1999. \nEncyclopedia.com. 15 Apr. 2009 <http://www.encyclopedia.com>{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}.\n</ref> In many respects, especially the anatomy of the lower jaw, ''Anthracotherium'', as with other members of the family, is allied to the hippopotamus, of which it is probably an ancestral form.<ref>Nature 450, 1190-1194 (20 December 2007) | {{doi|10.1038/nature06343}}; Received 26 June 2007; Accepted 3 October 2007\n</ref>\nHowever, one study suggests, instead of anthracotheres, another pig-like group of artiodactyls, called [[palaeochoerid]]s, are the true [[stem group]] of [[Hippopotamidae]].<ref name=\"Pickford2008\">{{cite journal\n | last = Pickford | first = Martin\n | title = The myth of the hippo-like anthracothere: The eternal problem of homology and convergence\n | year = 2008 | journal = Revista Espa\u00f1ola de Paleontolog\u00eda\n | volume = 23 | issue = 1 | pages = 31\u201390 | issn = 0213-6937}}</ref>\n\nRecent evidence, gained from comparative gene sequencing, further suggests that hippos are the closest living relatives of whales,<ref name=\"DNA\">{{Cite journal | url = http://mbe.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/content/abstract/14/5/537 | title = More DNA support for a Cetacea/Hippopotamidae clade: the blood-clotting protein gene gamma-fibrinogen | author = Gatesy, J. | journal = [[Molecular Biology and Evolution]] | volume = 14 | pages = 537\u2013543 | pmid = 9159931 | issue = 5 | date=1 May 1997 | doi=10.1093/oxfordjournals.molbev.a025790}}</ref><ref name=\"Genomes\">{{Cite journal | title = Analyses of mitochondrial genomes strongly support a hippopotamus-whale clade | volume = 265 | issue = 1412 | year = 1998 | pages = 2251\u20135 | journal = [[Proceedings of the Royal Society]] | author = Ursing, B.M. |author2= U. Arnason | doi = 10.1098/rspb.1998.0567 | pmid = 9881471 | pmc = 1689531}}</ref> so, if anthracotheres are stem hippos, they would also be related to whales in a clade provisionally called [[Whippomorpha]].\n\nHowever, the earliest known anthracotheres appear in the fossil record in the middle [[Eocene]], well after the [[archaeoceti|archaeocetes]] had taken up totally aquatic lifestyles. Although phylogenetic analyses of molecular data on extant animals strongly support the notion that hippopotamids are the closest relatives of cetaceans (whales, dolphins and porpoises), the two groups are unlikely to be closely related when extant and extinct artiodactyls are analyzed. Cetaceans originated about 50 million years ago in south Asia, whereas the family Hippopotamidae is only 15 million years old, and the first hippopotamids are only 6 million years old. Yet, analyses of fossil clades have not resolved the issue of cetacean relations.<ref>{{Cite journal\n | last1 = Thewissen | first1 = JGM\n | last2 = Cooper | first2 = Lisa Noelle\n | last3 = Clementz | first3 = Mark T\n | last4 = Bajpai | first4 = Sunil\n | last5 = Tiwari |first5=BN\n | title = Whales originated from aquatic artiodactyls in the Eocene epoch of India\n |date=20 December 2007 | journal = Nature | volume = 450 | issue = 7173 | pages = 1190\u20134\n | url = http://www.masonposner.com/media/evolution/thewissen2007.pdf | accessdate = 24 June 2009 \n | doi = 10.1038/nature06343 | pmid = 18097400 | oclc = 264243832 | bibcode=2007Natur.450.1190T}}</ref>\n\nAnother study has offered a suggestion that anthracotheres are part of a clade that also consists of [[entelodont]]s (and even ''[[Andrewsarchus]]'') and that is a sister clade to other cetancodonts, with ''[[Siamotherium]]'' as the most basal member of the clade [[Cetacodontamorpha]].<ref>{{cite journal|pmc=2740860 | pmid=19774069|year=2009|last1=Spaulding|first1=M|last2=O'Leary|first2=MA|last3=Gatesy|first3=J|title=Relationships of Cetacea (Artiodactyla) Among Mammals: Increased Taxon Sampling Alters Interpretations of Key Fossils and Character Evolution|volume=4|issue=9|pages=e7062|doi=10.1371/journal.pone.0007062|journal=PLOS ONE|editor1-last=Farke|editor1-first=Andrew Allen|bibcode = 2009PLoSO...4.7062S }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q574319}}\n\n[[Category:Anthracotheres| ]]\n[[Category:Piacenzian extinctions]]\n[[Category:Eocene first appearances]]\n[[Category:Danielle is Gem]]\n", "text_old": "{{Automatic taxobox\n| fossil_range = {{Fossil range|Middle Eocene|Late Pliocene}}\n| image = Anthracotherium magnum.jpg\n| image_upright = 1.15\n| image_caption = ''[[Anthracotherium]]''\n| taxon = Anthracotheriidae\n| authority = [[Joseph Leidy|Leidy]], 1869\n| subdivision_ranks = Subfamilies and genera<ref name=KronMan>{{cite book |last=Kron, D.G. |first=B. |author2=Manning, E. |editor1=Janis, C.M. |editor2=Scott, K.M. |editor3=Jacobs, L.L. |title=Evolution of Tertiary mammals of North America |edition= |year=1998 |publisher=Cambridge University Press |location=Cambridge |isbn=978-0-521-35519-3 |pages=381\u2013388 |chapter=Anthracotheriidae }}</ref><ref name=\"PNAS on Anthracotheres\">{{Cite journal |author1=Lihoreau, Fabrice |author2=Jean-Renaud Boisserie |display-authors=etal | title = Anthracothere dental anatomy reveals a late Miocene Chado-Libyan bioprovince | journal = [[Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences]] | issue = originally published online May 24, 2006 | language = |url=http://www.pnas.org/cgi/reprint/103/23/8763.pdf |doi=10.1073/pnas.0603126103 | pmid=16723392 | year = 2006 | volume = 103 | pages = 8763\u20137 | pmc = 1482652|bibcode = 2006PNAS..103.8763L }}</ref>\n| subdivision = \n\u2020 Anthracotheriinae\n*\u2020''[[Anthracotherium]]'' <small>([[type genus]])</small>\n*\u2020''[[Heptacodon]]''\n*\u2020''[[Siamotherium]]''\n\u2020 Bothriodontinae\n*\u2020''[[Aepinacodon]]''\n*\u2020''[[Afromeryx]]''\n*\u2020''[[Arretotherium]]''\n*\u2020''[[Brachyodus]]''\n*\u2020''[[Bothriogenys]]''\n*\u2020''[[Elomeryx]]''\n*\u2020''[[Hemimeryx]]''\n*\u2020''[[Kukusepasutanka]]''\n*\u2020''[[Libycosaurus]]''\n*\u2020''[[Merycopotamus]]''\n*\u2020''[[Sivameryx]]''\n\u2020 Microbunodontinae\n*\u2020''[[Anthracokeryx]]''\n*\u2020''[[Microbunodon]]''\n}}\n\n'''Anthracotheriidae''' is a family of extinct, [[hippopotamus]]-like [[artiodactyl]] [[ungulate]]s related to [[hippopotamus]]es and [[Cetacea|whale]]s. The oldest genus, ''[[Elomeryx]]'', first appeared during the middle [[Eocene]] in Asia. They thrived in Africa and Eurasia, with a few species ultimately entering [[North America]] during the [[Oligocene]]. They died out in Europe and Africa during the [[Miocene]], possibly due to a combination of climatic changes and competition with other artiodactyls, including pigs and true hippopotamuses.<ref name=\"zipcodezoo.com\">{{cite web|url=http://zipcodezoo.com/Key/Animalia/Anthracotheriidae_Family.asp |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-04-30 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090319081544/http://zipcodezoo.com/Key/Animalia/Anthracotheriidae_Family.asp |archivedate=2009-03-19 }}</ref> The youngest genus, ''[[Merycopotamus]]'', died out in Asia during the late [[Pliocene]]. The family is named after the first [[genus]] discovered, ''[[Anthracotherium]]'', which means \"coal beast\", as the first fossils of it were found in [[Paleogene]]-aged coal beds in [[France]]. Fossil remains of the anthracothere genus were discovered by the Harvard University and Geological Survey of Pakistan joint research project (Y-GSP) in the well-dated middle and late Miocene deposits of the [[Pothohar Plateau]] in northern Pakistan.<ref>[], Chaire de Pal\u00e9oanthropologie et de Pr\u00e9histoire, Coll\u00e8ge de France, 11 place Marcelin Berthelot, 75005 Paris, France \nCopyright 2007 The Palaeontological Association\n</ref>\n\nIn life, the average anthracothere would have resembled a skinny hippopotamus with a comparatively small, narrow head and most likely pig-like in general appearance.<ref>{{cite web\n  | last = Allaby\n  | first = Michael \n  | title = Anthracotheriidae\n  | work = A Dictionary of Zoology\n  | publisher =  Encyclopedia.com\n  | year = 1999\n  | url = http://www.encyclopedia.com/doc/1O8-Anthracotheriidae.html\n  | doi =\n  | accessdate = 15 Apr 2009}}</ref> They had four or five toes on each foot, and broad feet suited to walking on soft mud. They had full sets of about 44 teeth with five semicrescentric cusps on the upper molars,<ref name=\"zipcodezoo.com\" /> which, in some species, were adapted for digging up the roots of aquatic plants.<ref>{{cite book |editor=Palmer, D.|year=1999 |title= The Marshall Illustrated Encyclopedia of Dinosaurs and Prehistoric Animals|publisher= Marshall Editions| location=London|isbn= 978-1-84028-152-1 |author1=Douglas Palmer |author2=consultant editor Barry Cox |page= 268}}</ref>\n\n==Evolutionary relationships==\n[[File:Microbunodon.JPG|thumb|left|''Microbunodon'' skull]]\nSome skeletal characters of anthracotheres suggest they are related to hippos.<ref name=\"Cetartiodactyla\">{{cite journal |last=Boisserie |first=Jean-Renaud |author2= Fabrice Lihoreau |author3=Michel Brunet |date=February 2005|title= The position of Hippopotamidae within Cetartiodactyla|journal= [[Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences]] |volume= 102 |issue= 5|pages= 1537\u20131541|doi= 10.1073/pnas.0409518102 |pmid=15677331 |pmc=547867|bibcode = 2005PNAS..102.1537B }}</ref>\nThe nature of the sediments in which they are fossilized implies they were amphibious, which supports the view, based on anatomical evidence, that they were ancestors of the hippopotamuses.<ref>Michael Allaby. \"Anthracotheriidae.\" ''A Dictionary of Zoology''. 1999. \nEncyclopedia.com. 15 Apr. 2009 <http://www.encyclopedia.com>{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}.\n</ref> In many respects, especially the anatomy of the lower jaw, ''Anthracotherium'', as with other members of the family, is allied to the hippopotamus, of which it is probably an ancestral form.<ref>Nature 450, 1190-1194 (20 December 2007) | {{doi|10.1038/nature06343}}; Received 26 June 2007; Accepted 3 October 2007\n</ref>\nHowever, one study suggests, instead of anthracotheres, another pig-like group of artiodactyls, called [[palaeochoerid]]s, are the true [[stem group]] of [[Hippopotamidae]].<ref name=\"Pickford2008\">{{cite journal\n | last = Pickford | first = Martin\n | title = The myth of the hippo-like anthracothere: The eternal problem of homology and convergence\n | year = 2008 | journal = Revista Espa\u00f1ola de Paleontolog\u00eda\n | volume = 23 | issue = 1 | pages = 31\u201390 | issn = 0213-6937}}</ref>\n\nRecent evidence, gained from comparative gene sequencing, further suggests that hippos are the closest living relatives of whales,<ref name=\"DNA\">{{Cite journal | url = http://mbe.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/content/abstract/14/5/537 | title = More DNA support for a Cetacea/Hippopotamidae clade: the blood-clotting protein gene gamma-fibrinogen | author = Gatesy, J. | journal = [[Molecular Biology and Evolution]] | volume = 14 | pages = 537\u2013543 | pmid = 9159931 | issue = 5 | date=1 May 1997 | doi=10.1093/oxfordjournals.molbev.a025790}}</ref><ref name=\"Genomes\">{{Cite journal | title = Analyses of mitochondrial genomes strongly support a hippopotamus-whale clade | volume = 265 | issue = 1412 | year = 1998 | pages = 2251\u20135 | journal = [[Proceedings of the Royal Society]] | author = Ursing, B.M. |author2= U. Arnason | doi = 10.1098/rspb.1998.0567 | pmid = 9881471 | pmc = 1689531}}</ref> so, if anthracotheres are stem hippos, they would also be related to whales in a clade provisionally called [[Whippomorpha]].\n\nHowever, the earliest known anthracotheres appear in the fossil record in the middle [[Eocene]], well after the [[archaeoceti|archaeocetes]] had taken up totally aquatic lifestyles. Although phylogenetic analyses of molecular data on extant animals strongly support the notion that hippopotamids are the closest relatives of cetaceans (whales, dolphins and porpoises), the two groups are unlikely to be closely related when extant and extinct artiodactyls are analyzed. Cetaceans originated about 50 million years ago in south Asia, whereas the family Hippopotamidae is only 15 million years old, and the first hippopotamids are only 6 million years old. Yet, analyses of fossil clades have not resolved the issue of cetacean relations.<ref>{{Cite journal\n | last1 = Thewissen | first1 = JGM\n | last2 = Cooper | first2 = Lisa Noelle\n | last3 = Clementz | first3 = Mark T\n | last4 = Bajpai | first4 = Sunil\n | last5 = Tiwari |first5=BN\n | title = Whales originated from aquatic artiodactyls in the Eocene epoch of India\n |date=20 December 2007 | journal = Nature | volume = 450 | issue = 7173 | pages = 1190\u20134\n | url = http://www.masonposner.com/media/evolution/thewissen2007.pdf | accessdate = 24 June 2009 \n | doi = 10.1038/nature06343 | pmid = 18097400 | oclc = 264243832 | bibcode=2007Natur.450.1190T}}</ref>\n\nAnother study has offered a suggestion that anthracotheres are part of a clade that also consists of [[entelodont]]s (and even ''[[Andrewsarchus]]'') and that is a sister clade to other cetancodonts, with ''[[Siamotherium]]'' as the most basal member of the clade [[Cetacodontamorpha]].<ref>{{cite journal|pmc=2740860 | pmid=19774069|year=2009|last1=Spaulding|first1=M|last2=O'Leary|first2=MA|last3=Gatesy|first3=J|title=Relationships of Cetacea (Artiodactyla) Among Mammals: Increased Taxon Sampling Alters Interpretations of Key Fossils and Character Evolution|volume=4|issue=9|pages=e7062|doi=10.1371/journal.pone.0007062|journal=PLOS ONE|editor1-last=Farke|editor1-first=Andrew Allen|bibcode = 2009PLoSO...4.7062S }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q574319}}\n\n[[Category:Anthracotheres| ]]\n[[Category:Piacenzian extinctions]]\n[[Category:Eocene first appearances]]\n", "name_user": "2607:fea8:f460:4820:68f4:e900:a783:c6bd", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Added danielle is gem.)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anthracotheriidae"}
