ase because of a dead ball caused by the rain, Mihashi and the rest of his team work hard in order to get one more run before the inning ends.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 19\n| Title               = T\u014dsei\u2019s Real Power\n| TranslitTitle       = T\u014dsei no Jitsuryoku\n| NativeTitle         = \u6850\u9752\u306e\u5b9f\u529b\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2007|8|16}}\n| ShortSummary        = T\u014dsei continues with their attack plan, concentrating on hitting Mihashi\u2019s curveball, and manage to get in one run. Nishiura gets into a little mishap, because Mihashi gets a nose bleed, making Abe worry about Mihashi\u2019s condition and whether or not he can pitch. However, it was lucky that this didn\u2019t happen until after the 5th inning, so Mihashi was able to rest for a bit while the field underwent maintenance. The 6th inning doesn\u2019t progress much better for Nishiura, as T\u014dsei ties the score.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 20\n| Title               = Turning the Tables\n| TranslitTitle       = Gyakuten\n| NativeTitle         = \u9006\u8ee2\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2007|8|23}}\n| ShortSummary        = Though Nishiura is playing a good defence, the lucky breaks that T\u014dsei keep on having make the members of Nishiura seem clumsy. The mound becomes slipper as the rain pours down harder, causing Mihashi to lose his footing and throw a wild pitch, giving T\u014dsei the opportunity to steal another run. To make matters worse, Mihashi\u2019s fever is rising, but after Ruri tells him that Kan\u014d and Mihoshi won their game, \"Ren-Ren\" has renewed strength and will to pitch the rest of the game.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 21\n| Title               = One More Run\n| TranslitTitle       = M\u014d Itten\n| NativeTitle         = \u3082\u3046\u4e00\u70b9\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2007|8|30}}\n| ShortSummary        = Tajima once again strikes out, but is able to help his team mates successfully steal bases once he enters the coaching box again. With a nice hit from Mizutani, Suyama gains another point for Nishiura. Hanai also tries to steal another run on the same play, but is stopped by Kawai. Tajima feels down because he hasn\u2019t been able to contribute any runs, but the other guys cheer him up by saying that they will get him another chance to bat once more.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 22\n| Title               = Defense!\n| TranslitTitle       = Fusege!\n| NativeTitle         = \u9632\u3052!\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2007|9|6}}\n| ShortSummary        = T\u014dsei takes several gamble plays and is able to get one more run in to take the lead once again. On the second attempt at a run, Mihashi paused briefly before throwing the ball back home, for he was afraid that Abe would be injured. Abe got angry with Mihashi but assured him that he would keep his promise not to be injured.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 23\n| Title               = Precisely\n| TranslitTitle       = Genmitsu ni\n| NativeTitle         = \u30b2\u30f3\u30df\u30c4\u306b\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2007|9|13}}\n| ShortSummary        = Nishiura is desperate now to get their batters onto the plates in order to have a chance at winning. The team hangs in the game long enough for Tajima to have one more at bat chance, with two runners on third and second base, and two outs. Tajima is finally able to hit Takase\u2019s sinker, thus allowing Nishiura to take back the lead with two runs.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 24\n| Title               = The End of the Game\n| TranslitTitle       = Ketchaku\n| NativeTitle         = \u6c7a\u7740\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2007|9|20}}\n| ShortSummary        = Now that they have the lead, Nishiura must make sure that they don\u2019t allow any more runs. Abe wants Mihashi to keep pitching his fastball, but Mihashi feels insecure, and is practically out of gas. Even still, Mihashi does not want to get off the mount and sticks in there until the very end. After losing the game, T\u014dsei is devastated but manage to congratulate Nishiura. Mihashi falls into a deep sleep after the game. T\u014dsei's back up catcher runs into Tajima and asks for his email address because he is in such awe of him\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 25\n| Title               = After One Win\n| TranslitTitle       = Hitotsu Katte\n| NativeTitle         = \u3072\u3068\u3064\u52dd\u3063\u3066\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2007|9|27}}\n| ShortSummary        = Taking place one day after the big game, Mihashi is still sick and is ignoring Abe's text messages thinking he is mad at him for not giving up the mound. However, Tajima reveals that he and Izumi and going to Mihashi's for curry and Hanai and Abe tag along. Abe begins to mull over why Mihashi is ignoring him and concludes that perhaps Mihashi hates him. When they arrive at the house, Mihashi reveals he has lost 3kg making Abe furious and he begins to yell at Mihashi but stops and changes tactics which confuses Mihashi more. Tajima also reveals that he hurt his hand during his last at bat.  As the boys eat, they reveal the reasons they all chose Nishiura and watch the recap of the games.  Mihashi apologizes for not giving up the mound and Abe tells him that it was a lie, he never wanted him to give up the mound. Hanai shows Mihashi notes from the team meeting and the notes reveal how everyone praises Mihashi's pitching and he is shocked that they think so highly of him.  Later, Mihashi calls Kan\u014d and reports their win.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = OVA\n| Title               = The Basics of Basics\n| TranslitTitle       = Kihon no Kihon\n| NativeTitle         = \u57fa\u672c\u306e\u30ad\u30db\u30f3\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = Unaired (DVD Only) or (Funimation's Official Website & YouTube Channel)\n| ShortSummary        = (One year before the beginning of the story) Kaguyama feels intimidated by Haruna\u2019s presence on the baseball team for he feels that his positioned as the ace pitcher is threatened. Kaguyama wants to quit, but Haruna talks him out of it after telling Kaguyama about his own past.\n}}\n|}\n\n===\u014ckiku Furikabutte ~Natsu no Taikai-hen~ (2010)===\n{{Expand list|date=August 2010}}\n{|class=\"wikitable\" width=\"98%\"\n|-\n! # !! Title !! Original air date\n|-\n| colspan=\"5\" bgcolor=\"#CCF\"|\n|-\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 01\n| Title               = What's Next?\n| TranslitTitle       = Tsugi Wa?\n| NativeTitle         = \u6b21\u306f\uff1f\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2010|4|1}}\n| ShortSummary        = The episode begins with a combo play by Tajima and Mihashi in a gym period soccer game. Meanwhile, Shinooka is approached by her friends to become cheerleaders for the clubs ouendan.\nDuring lunch break Mihashi, Izumi, Hanada and Tajima discuss the eventuality of making it into the news when Hanada brings up Momoe-san in the conversation over food.\nThe team later attends a match between two schools, where the winner is scheduled to be Nishiura'a next opponent.\nMomoe-san also reveals the positions for the next game and displays her persuasive skills in convincing the injured Tajima to give up the cleanup hitter spot\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 02\n| Title               = Sakitama\n| TranslitTitle       = Sakitama\n| NativeTitle         = \u5d0e\u7389\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2010|4|8}}\n| ShortSummary        = The episode continues where the last one left off, i.e. with the Nishiura team watching the Sakitama match and is set off with the arrival of Mrs. Hanai