ure_high   = \n| temperature_low    = \n| frozen             = \n| islands            = \n| islands_category   = \n| sections           = \n| trenches           = \n| benches            = \n| cities             = \n| pushpin_map             = Canada Ontario\n| pushpin_label_position  = <!-- left, right, top or bottom -->\n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in Ontario\n| website            = \n| reference          = \n}}\n\n'''Ulster Lake''' ({{lang-fr|lac Ulster}}) is a [[lake]] in the municipality of [[Sioux Narrows-Nestor Falls]], [[Rainy River District]] in [[Northwestern Ontario|northwestern]] [[Ontario]], [[Canada]].<ref name=\"CGNDB\" /><ref name=\"AOCToporama\" /><ref name=\"OntGeoNamesMap\">{{cite web|url= http://www.gisapplication.lrc.gov.on.ca/Geonames/Index.html?site=Geographic_Names&viewer=Geonames&locale=en-US |title= Ontario Geonames GIS (on-line map and search)|publisher= [[Ministry of Natural Resources and Forestry|Ontario Ministry of Natural Resources and Forestry]]|date= 2014|access-date= 2020-04-09}}</ref><ref name=\"OntarioRoadMap\">{{cite map|url= http://www.mto.gov.on.ca/english/publications/official-road-map/pdfs/map-13.pdf |format= PDF|title= Map 13|series= Official road map of Ontario|publisher= [[Ministry of Transportation of Ontario]]|scale= 1 : 1,600,000|date= 2018-01-01|accessdate= 2020-04-09}}</ref><ref name=\"Restructuring\">{{cite map|url= http://www.mah.gov.on.ca/AssetFactory.aspx?did=6572 |title= Restructured municipalities - Ontario map #1|year= 2006|series= Restructuring Maps of Ontario|publisher= [[Ministry of Municipal Affairs and Housing (Ontario)|Ontario Ministry of Municipal Affairs and Housing]]|accessdate= 2020-04-09}}</ref> It is part of the [[Hudson Bay drainage basin]].<ref name=\"AOCToporama\" /><ref name=\"OntGeoNamesMap\" />\n\nThe primary inflow is the [[Black River (Kenora District)|Black River]] at the east. The primary outflow is also the [[Black River (Kenora District)|Black River]] which flows from the southern tip of the lake via the [[Lake of the Woods]], the [[Winnipeg River]] and the [[Nelson River]] to [[Hudson Bay]].<ref name=\"CGNDB\" /><ref name=\"AOCToporama\" /><ref name=\"OntGeoNamesMap\" />\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of lakes in Ontario]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Lakes of Kenora District]]\n{{Ontario-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox body of water\n| name               = Ulster Lake\n| native_name        = \n| native_name_lang   = \n| other_name         = {{lang|fr|lac Ulster}}\n| image              = \n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| image_bathymetry   = \n| alt_bathymetry     = \n| caption_bathymetry = \n| location           = [[Kenora District]], [[Ontario]]\n| group              = \n| coordinates        = {{coord|49|34|48|N|93|59|43|W|region:CA-ON_type:waterbody|notes=<ref name=\"CGNDB\">{{cite cgndb|id= FCYUJ|title= Ulster Lake|accessdate=2020-04-09}}</ref>|display=inline,title}}\n| type               = \n| etymology          = \n| part_of            = [[Hudson Bay drainage basin]]\n| inflow             = [[Black River (Kenora District)|Black River]]\n| rivers             = \n| outflow            = [[Black River (Kenora District)|Black River]]\n| oceans             = \n| catchment          = \n| basin_countries    = [[Canada]]\n| agency             = \n| designation        = \n| date-built         = <!-- {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} For man-made and other recent bodies of water -->\n| engineer           = \n| date-flooded       = <!-- {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} For man-made and other recent bodies of water -->\n| length             = {{convert|3|km|abbr=on}}<ref name=\"AOCToporama\">{{cite web|url= http://atlas.gc.ca/toporama/en/index.html |title= Toporama (on-line map and search)|work= [[Atlas of Canada]]|publisher= Natural Resources Canada|access-date= 2020-04-09}}</ref>\n| width              = {{convert|2|km|abbr=on}}<ref name=\"AOCToporama\" />\n| area               = \n| depth              = \n| max-depth          = \n| volume             = \n| residence_time     = \n| salinity           = \n| shore              = \n| elevation          = {{convert|372|m|abbr=on}}<ref name=\"GoogleEarthElev\">{{cite web|url= https://earth.google.com/web/|title= Google Earth|access-date= 2020-04-09}}</ref>\n| temperature_high   = \n| temperature_low    = \n| frozen             = \n| islands            = \n| islands_category   = \n| sections           = \n| trenches           = \n| benches            = \n| cities             = \n| pushpin_map             = Canada Ontario\n| pushpin_label_position  = <!-- left, right, top or bottom -->\n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in Ontario\n| website            = \n| reference          = \n}}\n\n'''Ulster Lake''' ({{lang-fr|lac Ulster}}) is a [[lake]] in the municipality of [[Sioux Narrows-Nestor Falls]], [[Rainy River District]] in [[Northwestern Ontario|northwestern]] [[Ontario]], [[Canada]].<ref name=\"CGNDB\" /><ref name=\"AOCToporama\" /><ref name=\"OntGeoNamesMap\">{{cite web|url= http://www.gisapplication.lrc.gov.on.ca/Geonames/Index.html?site=Geographic_Names&viewer=Geonames&locale=en-US |title= Ontario Geonames GIS (on-line map and search)|publisher= [[Ministry of Natural Resources and Forestry|Ontario Ministry of Natural Resources and Forestry]]|date= 2014|access-date= 2020-04-09}}</ref><ref name=\"OntarioRoadMap\">{{cite map|url= http://www.mto.gov.on.ca/english/publications/official-road-map/pdfs/map-13.pdf |format= PDF|title= Map 13|series= Official road map of Ontario|publisher= [[Ministry of Transportation of Ontario]]|scale= 1 : 1,600,000|date= 2018-01-01|accessdate= 2020-04-09}}</ref><ref name=\"Restructuring\">{{cite map|url= http://www.mah.gov.on.ca/AssetFactory.aspx?did=6572 |title= Restructured municipalities - Ontario map #1|year= 2006|series= Restructuring Maps of Ontario|publisher= [[Ministry of Municipal Affairs and Housing (Ontario)|Ontario Ministry of Municipal Affairs and Housing]]|accessdate= 2020-04-09}}</ref> It is part of the [[Hudson Bay drainage basin]].<ref name=\"AOCToporama\" /><ref name=\"OntGeoNamesMap\" />\n\nThe primary inflow is the [[Black River (Kenora District)|Black River]] at the east. The primary outflow is also the [[[[Black River (Kenora District)|Black River]] which flows from the southern tip of the lake via the [[Lake of the Woods]], the [[Winnipeg River]] and the [[Nelson River]] to [[Hudson Bay]].<ref name=\"CGNDB\" /><ref name=\"AOCToporama\" /><ref name=\"OntGeoNamesMap\" />\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of lakes in Ontario]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Lakes of Rainy River District]]\n{{Ontario-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Qui1che", "label": "safe", "comment": "typo; corrected category", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ulster_Lake_(Kenora_District)"}
{"title_page": "Illumitoon Entertainment", "text_new": "{{Infobox company\n| name             = Illumitoon Entertainment\n| logo             = \n| type             = [[Privately held company|Private]]<ref name=am07112006form/>\n| fate             = Defunct\n| genre            = [[Anime]]<ref name=am07112006form/>\n| foundation       = 2006<ref name=ann07122006beetpr/>\n| founder          = Stephanie Giotes, Richard Ray, and [[Barry Watson (producer)|Barry Watson]]<ref name=am07112006form/>\n | defunct         = {{end date and age|2007}}\n| location_city    = [[Fort Worth, Texas]]\n| location_country = United States<ref name=am07112006form/>\n| key_people       = Barry Watson <small>President/[[Chief executive officer|CEO]]</small><ref name=am07112006form/>\n| divisions        = \n| homepage         = \n}}\n\n'''Illumitoon Entertainment''' was a production company based in [[Fort Worth, Texas]] that specialized in [[anime]]. It was founded in January 2006 by former [[Funimation]] executives Stephanie Giotes, Richard Ray, and [[Barry Watson (producer)|Barry Watson]].<ref name=am07112006form/><ref name=ann07122006beetpr/> Illumitoon's goal was to have its shows aired on television and offer unedited dual language DVDs.<ref name=ann08122012bobowrong/><ref name=ann02222013answerman/>\n\n==History==\nIllumitoon shared facilities with CRM Productions in [[Fort Worth, Texas]] and [[Westlake Entertainment]] was used for distribution.<ref name=am07112006form/><ref name=ann09072006west/> The company's first anime license was [[Beet the Vandel Buster]] and Beet the Vandel Buster Excellion.<ref name=ann07122006beet/> They also licensed [[AM Driver]], [[B't X]], and BT'X Neo.<ref name=ann08232006amdriver/><ref name=ann09192006btx/> Illumitoon joined with Westlake for the licensing of [[Bobobo-bo Bo-bobo]].<ref name=ann11022006bobobobo/><ref name=am11092006bobo/> Several Illumitoon releases had production issues including music being changed, the use of dubtitles (subtitles created from the dub script), and inoperable discs.<ref name=ann08122012bobowrong/><ref name=ann02222013answerman/><ref name=ann02122007shelf/><ref name=ann03252007review/><ref name=ann12312007shelf/> Replacements with translated subtitles were offered for the first DVDs of Beet, Bobo, and B't X that were later found to be DVD-Rs.<ref name=ann02222013answerman/><ref name=ann04022007rep/><ref name=an03302007rep/> AM Driver and B't X were licensed by [[Anime Network|The Anime Network]] for [[Video on demand|VOD]], but only 14 episodes of each series had a complete dub.<ref name=ann02222013answerman/><ref name=icv208162007network/><ref name=ann08152007network/> After Westlake ceased distribution of their titles, future releases from Illumitoon were cancelled in late 2007.<ref name=ann02222013answerman/><ref name=ann10262007future/>\n\n==Post Illumitoon==\nAM Driver was never released on DVD and all series remained incomplete until S'more Entertainment relicensed Bobobo-bo Bo-bobo.<ref name=ann02222013answerman/><ref name=ann01162012bobosmore/> This release also experienced issues due to the lack of subtitles.<ref name=ann08122012bobowrong/><ref name=ann02222013answerman/> B't X was relicensed in 2016 by [[Anime Midstream]].<ref name=ann08192016btxam/><ref name=tfp08192016btxam/>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Funimation]]\n* [[Westlake Entertainment]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2|refs=\n\n<ref name=am07112006form>{{cite news|last1=Ball|first1=Ryan|title=Ex-FUNimation Execs Form Illumitoon|url=http://www.animationmagazine.net/tv/ex-funimation-execs-form-illumitoon/|accessdate=14 March 2015|work=Animation Magazine|date=July 11, 2006}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=am11092006bobo>{{cite news|last1=Ball|first1=Ryan|title=Illumitoon, Westlake Pick Up Bobobo|url=http://www.animationmagazine.net/home-entertainment/illumitoon-westlake-pick-up-bobobo/|accessdate=14 March 2015|work=Animation Magazine|date=November 9, 2006}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=ann07122006beet>{{cite news|title=Illumitoon Lights Up With B