 DVD Replacement Offer|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2007-04-02/illumitoons-dvd-replacement-offer|accessdate=13 March 2015|work=Anime News Network|date=April 2, 2007}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=ann08152007network>{{cite news|title=Anime Network Licenses New Television Programming from Illumitoon Entertainment|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/press-release/2007-08-15/anime-network-licenses-new-television-programming-from-illumitoon-entertainment|accessdate=13 March 2015|work=Anime News Network|date=August 15, 2007}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=ann10262007future>{{cite news|title=Illumitoon's B'tX, Beet, BoBoBo-Bo DVDs Discontinued (Updated)|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2007-10-26/illumitoon%27s-b%27tx-beet-bobobo-bo-dvds-discontinued|accessdate=14 March 2015|work=Anime News Network|date=October 26, 2007}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=ann12312007shelf>{{cite news|last1=Dong|first1=Bamboo|title=Shelf Life - Year in Reviews|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/shelf-life/2007-12-31|accessdate=14 March 2015|work=Anime News Network|date=December 31, 2007}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=ann01162012bobosmore>{{cite news|title=S'more Entertainment Adds Bobobo-bo Bo-bobo on U.S. DVD|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2012-01-16/smore-entertainment-adds-bobobo-bo-bo-bobo-on-u.s-dvd|accessdate=13 March 2015|work=Anime News Network|date=January 16, 2012}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=ann08122012bobowrong>{{cite news|last1=Toole|first1=Michael|title=The Mike Toole Show - Getting It Wrong|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/the-mike-toole-show/2012-08-12|accessdate=14 March 2015|work=Anime News Network|date=August 12, 2012}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=ann02222013answerman>{{cite news|last1=Hanson|first1=Brian|title=Hey, Answerman! - Translation Mitigation|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/answerman/2013-02-22|accessdate=14 March 2015|work=Anime News Network|date=February 22, 2013}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=ann08192016btxam>{{cite news|title=Anime Midstream Licenses B't X TV Anime Series|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-08-19/anime-midstream-licenses-bt-x-tv-anime-series/.105546|accessdate=12 October 2016|work=Anime News Network|date=August 19, 2016}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=an03302007rep>{{cite news|title=Illumitoon Announces Disc Replacement Offer|url=http://www.animenation.net/illumitoon-announces-disc-replacement-offer/|accessdate=13 March 2015|work=AnimeNation|date=March 30, 2007}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=icv208162007network>{{cite news|title=The Anime Network Adds Illumitoon Titles|url=http://icv2.com/articles/news/view/11127/the-anime-network-adds-illumitoon-titles|accessdate=14 March 2015|work=ICv2|date=August 16, 2007}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=tfp08192016btxam>{{cite news|last1=Beveridge|first1=Chris|title=Anime Midstream Acquires \u2018B\u2019t X\u2019 Anime License|url=http://www.fandompost.com/2016/08/19/anime-midstream-acquires-bt-x-anime-license/|accessdate=12 October 2016|work=The Fandom Post|date=August 19, 2016}}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n==Further reading==\n*[[Newtype USA]] January 2007 - Vol. 6 No. 1 \"Bobobo-bo on DVD\". p.&nbsp;21\n\n== External links ==\n*{{ann|company|5896}}\n\n[[Category:Anime companies]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Fort Worth, Texas]]\n[[Category:Companies established in 2006]]\n\n{{anime-org-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox company\n| name             = Illumitoon Entertainment\n| logo             = \n| type             = [[Privately held company|Private]]<ref name=am07112006form/>\n| fate             = Defunct\n| genre            = [[Anime]]<ref name=am07112006form/>\n| foundation       = 2006<ref name=ann07122006beetpr/>\n| founder          = Stephanie Giotes, Richard Ray, and [[Barry Watson (producer)|Barry Watson]]<ref name=am07112006form/>\n | defunct         = {{end date and age|2007}}\n| location_city    = [[Fort Worth, Texas]]\n| location_country = United States<ref name=am07112006form/>\n| key_people       = Barry Watson <small>President/[[Chief executive officer|CEO]]</small><ref name=am07112006form/>\n| divisions        = \n| homepage         = \n}}\n\n'''Illumitoon Entertainment''' was a production company based in [[Fort Worth, Texas]] that specialized in [[anime]]. It was founded in January 2006 by former [[Funimation]] executives Stephanie Giotes, Richard Ray, and [[Barry Watson (producer)|Barry Watson]].<ref name=am07112006form/><ref name=ann07122006beetpr/> Illumitoon's goal was to have its shows aired on television and offer unedited dual language DVDs.<ref name=ann08122012bobowrong/><ref name=ann02222013answerman/>\n\n==History==\nIllumitoon shared facilities with CRM Productions in [[Fort Worth, Texas]] and [[Westlake Entertainment]] was used for distribution.<ref name=am07112006form/><ref name=ann09072006west/> The company's first anime license was [[Beet the Vandel Buster]] and Beet the Vandel Buster Excellion.<ref name=ann07122006beet/> They also licensed [[AM Driver]], [[B't X]], and BT'X Neo.<ref name=ann08232006amdriver/><ref name=ann09192006btx/> Illumitoon joined with Westlake for the licensing of [[Bobobo-bo Bo-bobo]].<ref name=ann11022006bobobobo/><ref name=am11092006bobo/> Several Illumitoon releases had production issues including music being changed, the use of dubtitles (subtitles created from the dub script), and inoperable discs.<ref name=ann08122012bobowrong/><ref name=ann02222013answerman/><ref name=ann02122007shelf/><ref name=ann03252007review/><ref name=ann12312007shelf/> Replacements with translated subtitles were offered for the first DVD's of Beet, Bobo, and B't X that were later found to be DVD-Rs.<ref name=ann02222013answerman/><ref name=ann04022007rep/><ref name=an03302007rep/> AM Driver and B't X were licensed by [[Anime Network|The Anime Network]] for [[Video on demand|VOD]], but only 14 episodes of each series had a complete dub.<ref name=ann02222013answerman/><ref name=icv208162007network/><ref name=ann08152007network/> After Westlake ceased distribution of their titles, future releases from Illumitoon were cancelled in late 2007.<ref name=ann02222013answerman/><ref name=ann10262007future/>\n\n==Post Illumitoon==\nAM Driver was never released on DVD and all series remained incomplete until S'more Entertainment relicensed Bobobo-bo Bo-bobo.<ref name=ann02222013answerman/><ref name=ann01162012bobosmore/> This release also experienced issues due to the lack of subtitles.<ref name=ann08122012bobowrong/><ref name=ann02222013answerman/> B't X was relicensed in 2016 by [[Anime Midstream]].<ref name=ann08192016btxam/><ref name=tfp08192016btxam/>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Funimation]]\n* [[Westlake Entertainment]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2|refs=\n\n<ref name=am07112006form>{{cite news|last1=Ball|first1=Ryan|title=Ex-FUNimation Execs Form Illumitoon|url=http://www.animationmagazine.net/tv/ex-funimation-execs-form-illumitoon/|accessdate=14 March 2015|work=Animation Magazine|date=July 11, 2006}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=am11092006bobo>{{cite news|last1=Ball|first1=Ryan|title=Illumitoon, Westlake Pick Up Bobobo|url=http://www.animationmagazine.net/home-entertainment/illumitoon-westlake-pick-up-bobobo/|accessdate=14 March 2015|work=Animation Magazine|date=November 9, 2006}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=ann07122006beet>{{cite news|title=Illumitoon Lights Up With Beet the Vandel Buster|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2006-07-12/illumitoon-lights-up-with-beet-the-vandel-buster|accessdate=12 March 2015|work=Anime News Network|date=July 12, 2006}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=ann07122006beetpr>{{cite news|title=Beet the Vandel Buster Coming to US|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/press-release/2006-07-12/beet-the-vandel-buster-coming-to-us|accessdate=12 March 2015|work=Anime News Network|date=July 12, 2006}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=ann08232006amdriver>{{cite news|title=Illumitoon Picks up AM Driver|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2006-08-23/illumitoon-picks-up-am-driver|accessdate=12 March 2015|work=Anime News Network|date=August 23, 2006}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=ann09072006west>{{cite news|title=Illumitoon Partners with Westlake|url=http://