umiko |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/major-development-plans-in-the-works-for-sentosa-and-pulau-brani |title=Major development plans in the works for Sentosa and Pulau Brani |website=The Straits Times |access-date=2 July 2019 |date=18 October 2018}}</ref>\n**The [[Health Promotion Board]] announced that there are multiple unauthorised log-in attempts into the HealthHub portal, which had 72 accounts successfully unlocked. As a result, access to HealthHub is temporarily stopped for five days.<ref>{{cite web |title=Multiple unauthorised log-in attempts detected on HealthHub portal: HPB |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/healthhub-log-in-attempts-hpb-accounts-hacked-cyberattack-10839168 |website=CNA |accessdate=25 July 2019 |date=18 October 2018}}</ref>\n* 19 October \u2013 Singapore signs a [[free trade agreement]] (FTA) with the [[European Union]] called the [[European Union\u2013Singapore Free Trade Agreement]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hussain |first1=Zakir |title=Singapore, European Union sign landmark free trade, partnership agreements |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/singapore-eu-sign-landmark-free-trade-partnership-agreements |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=7 July 2019 |date=20 October 2018}}</ref>\n* 23 October \u2013 [[Dyson (company)|Dyson]] plans to build [[electric cars]] in Singapore. The first vehicles are targeted to launch by 2021.<ref>{{cite web |title=British technology company Dyson to build electric car in Singapore |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/business/dyson-build-electric-car-singapore-10855708 |website=CNA |date=23 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181023133950/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/business/dyson-build-electric-car-singapore-10855708 |archive-date=23 October 2018 |accessdate=6 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last1=Tan |first1=Christopher |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/transport/fan-maker-dyson-to-build-electric-cars-in-singapore |titl